```
contract Foo {
  address _owner;

  modifier ownerOnly() {
    // The following test is commented out
    // require(msg.sender == _owner, "You are not the owner");
    _;            // Assume this is line 100
  }

  function f() external ownerOnly {
    require(false, "Can't call this method");
  }
}
```

The error will be shown with the location `_;` ("line 100" as labeled).

Additionally, the calling context (one stack frame deeper) does not always show in the stack trace when there is a revert. Often only the top stack frame shows, or the caller stack frame does not show. Yes, that could be an optimizer issue.

